{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/mthom/scryer-prolog/pulls/1880", "id": 1431002977, "node_id": "PR_kwDOBE6RW85VS19h", "html_url": "https://github.com/mthom/scryer-prolog/pull/1880", "diff_url": "https://github.com/mthom/scryer-prolog/pull/1880.diff", "patch_url": "https://github.com/mthom/scryer-prolog/pull/1880.patch", "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/mthom/scryer-prolog/issues/1880", "number": 1880, "state": "closed", "locked": false, "title": "Programatic use of Machine / Scryer as library", "user": {"login": "lucksus", "id": 311749, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjMxMTc0OQ==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/311749?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/lucksus", "html_url": "https://github.com/lucksus", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/lucksus/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/lucksus/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/lucksus/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/lucksus/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/lucksus/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/lucksus/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/lucksus/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/lucksus/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/lucksus/received_events", "type": "User", "user_view_type": "public", "site_admin": false}, "body": "These changes make it possible to run Prolog queries on a `Machine` instance in a 3rd-party crate that pulls-in Scryer as a library dependency, interfacing with the machine only with in-memory Strings.\r\n\r\n# Overview\r\n1. `Machine::run_input_once(&mut self)` runs the added toplevel predicate `run_input_once/0` which reads the query from user input like `repl` but just executes it once, returning/printing all results\r\n2. `Machine::load_module_string(&mut self, module_name: &str, program: String)` creates a stream from the given string and loads like a file\r\n3. `Machine::set_user_input(&mut self, input: String)` and `Machine::get_user_output(&self) -> String` enabling interfacing with the machine\r\n4. `Machine::run_query(&mut self, query: String) -> QueryResult` wraps it all up by setting the query as input and parsing the output string into added Rust type `QueryResult`.\r\n\r\n# Example usage\r\n```Rust\r\nlet mut machine = Machine::new_lib();\r\n\r\nmachine.load_module_string(\"facts\", String::from(r#\"\r\n    triple(\"a\", \"p1\", \"b\").\r\n    triple(\"a\", \"p2\", \"b\").\r\n\"#));\r\n\r\nlet output: QueryResult = machine.run_query(String::from(r#\"triple(\"a\",P,\"b\").\"#));\r\n\r\nassert_eq!(output, QueryResult::Matches(vec![\r\n    QueryMatch::from(btreemap!{\r\n        \"P\" => Value::from(\"p1\"),\r\n    }),\r\n    QueryMatch::from(btreemap!{\r\n        \"P\" => Value::from(\"p2\"),\r\n    }),\r\n]));\r\n ```\r\n\r\n# Next steps\r\n- [x] ensure parsing of complex result values\r\n- [x] `consult/1` like updating of machine state\r\n\r\n", "created_at": "2023-07-12T10:24:25Z", "updated_at": "2023-11-05T22:07:59Z", "closed_at": "2023-11-02T22:50:01Z", "merged_at": "2023-11-02T22:50:01Z", "merge_commit_sha": "575245c62f75d38e2bb66ebc233ae61bdb879347", "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "requested_reviewers": [], "requested_teams": [], "labels": [], "milestone": null, "draft": false, "commits_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/mthom/scryer-prolog/pulls/1880/commits", "review_comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/mthom/scryer-prolog/pulls/1880/comments", "review_comment_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/mthom/scryer-prolog/pulls/comments{/number}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/mthom/scryer-prolog/issues/1880/comments", "statuses_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/mthom/scryer-prolog/statuses/59264c0aa57de442fff16a82351ab4f5b8e6115d", "head": {"label": "coasys:library-use-case", "ref": "library-use-case", "sha": "59264c0aa57de